      {
        "block_label": "text",
        "block_content": "Our algorithm classifies a sample as being in the training set if  $ D(x, \\hat{x}) $ is smaller than a threshold  $ \\tau $, where  $ D(x, \\hat{x}) $ represents the difference between the two images. It can be calculated using traditional functions, such as the SSIM metric (Wang et al., 2004). Alternatively, we can train a neural network as a proxy. In Section 5, we will introduce the details of  $ D(x, \\hat{x}) $ used in our experiment.",
        "block_bbox": [
          618,
          923,
