      {
        "block_label": "text",
        "block_content": "Analysis We give a short analysis to justify why averaging over $n$ samples in REDIFFUSE can reduce the prediction error for training data. We have the following theorem showing that if we use the variation API to input a member $x \\sim D_{\\text{training}}$, then the error $\\|\\hat{x} - x\\|$ from our method will be small with high probability.",
